###Task: User System that can create a new user (first name, last name, username > tuple) or print all current users. We will use EasyGUI to ask our questions/makeusers and to print our list.

###Access EasyGUI
import easygui
###Screen/Output?

###List definitions
#current_users
cu = []
###User Data Types (Temporary)
##first_name
fn = ()
##last_name
ln = ()
##username
un = ()

title = "User System"

###Helper Functions
#MakeUser - Should ask for three inputs and store a tuple
def make_user():
    msg = "What's your first name?"
    fn = easygui.enterbox(msg, title)
    msg2 = "What's your last name?"
    ln = easygui.enterbox(msg2, title)
    msg3 = "What's your username?"
    un = easygui.enterbox(msg3, title)
    cu.append((fn, ln, un),)

